We are running into a loop overrun >1 second in auto init. The only thing being called is pathplanner buildAuto, so I am wondering if anyone has experienced a similar problem before and has a suggestion for what might be particularly inefficient about what I’m doing. Is there any way to warm up auto builder beforehand? Like calling getAutonomousCommand prior to auto init?

GitHub - FIRST-Team-1699/robocats2025 here is code (dev branch)

We had the exact same thing happen at competition. We reimaged our rio and moved getAutonomousCommand from autonomousInit to robotInit, which seemed to help, at least temporarily. See: PathPlanner first path going insane - HELP!

Two things that help:

  1. Run the warmup command in robotInit
  2. Load your autos in robot init, the run them when auto starts. Reading and parsing files is slow, so it’s best to do this ahead of time. The sendable chooser will do this.
